<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Fresno Climate</h2>
<p>For Fresno's hot-dry climate, high-efficiency systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher are recommended to manage the intense cooling demands cost-effectively. Heat pumps are particularly well-suited for Fresno, as they can efficiently cool during scorching summers and provide adequate heating during mild winters without the need for separate systems. Variable-speed compressors excel in this climate by running longer at lower speeds during extreme heat, maintaining consistent comfort while reducing energy spikes. Two-stage cooling systems also perform excellently, operating at lower capacity during moderate heat and full capacity during peak temperatures. Given Fresno's 4-6 month cooling season with temperatures above 90¬∞F, investing in 18+ SEER systems typically pays for itself through reduced electricity costs, especially with PG&E's tiered pricing structure that penalizes high usage.</p>

